<br>
If a planet several times larger than Jupiter were on a 40 degree elavated orbit with it's perihelion through the asteroid belt, I have to believe that there would be a signifigant wobble in either Mars, Jupiter, or their moons.  The lack of that would make a planet X a hard pill to swallow.<br>
