Harrington's work wasn't so much looking for Sitchin's planet X, every abstract I've read of his was trying to explain the perturbations of Neptune and searching for a 'planet' that lied out beyond it. These perturbations were disproven however when Voyager 2 passed and gave a more accurate number for the mass and density of Neptune which offset the 'perturbations argument'.  While Harrington was actively searching for a planetary body out beyond Neptune, it certaintly wasn't the planet X Sitchin described.<br>
